#### 7. Exception Handling in Tests (testsmells.org Smell #8)

**Method:** `ProcessOrder_EmptyOrder_ThrowsValidationError` (line 104)

```csharp
try {
    processor.ProcessOrder(order);
    Assert.Fail("Expected an exception but none was thrown");
} catch (ValidationException ex) {
    Assert.AreEqual("Order must contain at least one item", ex.Message);
}
```

**Problem:** Manual exception wiring is error-prone (e.g., catching a broader exception type accidentally masks bugs). MSTest provides `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` for exactly this purpose.

**Fix:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void ProcessOrder_EmptyOrder_ThrowsValidationError()
{
    var processor = new OrderProcessor(_db, _email, _inventory);
    var order = new Order();

    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ValidationException>(
        () => processor.ProcessOrder(order));

    Assert.AreEqual("Order must contain at least one item", ex.Message);
}
```

